<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="CRI02" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Joshua</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Cristall</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1768-04-22"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1847-10-18"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Godwin notes meeting 'Cristal' on several occasions, linked to Wollstonecraf, Johnson and others.  He also met his mother <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="CHR06">Elizabeth</persName>
    and his sister <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="CRI01">Anne </persName>. Anne's poetry was published by Joseph Johnson and there is evidence of her acquaintance with that circle. Joshua is 
    referred to on several occasions in Wollstonecrafts correspondence, with two being directed to him. The entries to 'Cristal' may be to Anne rather than her brother - but they
